 or topping of choice"]}],"id":"r285206","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-cxCwbarPJ_A\/XZaouZgHi7I\/AAAAAAAAhNA\/NiZzqKIRNqIQXaKfG39CWG6yNDduNd9CwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wR_EUcKjk2GY_X-g.png","title":"Sweet Potato Crust Pizza","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"18.5 g","fat":"23 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"34.2 g","calories":"1825 kJ \/ 437 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rolling pin, baking trays, baking paper, oven, grill","hintsAndTricks":["An alternative gluten-free pizza base that's easy with Thermomix®. In this nutritious option you make your own chickpea flour before mixing it with steamed sweet potatoes to create a simple yet tasty allergy-friendly pizza base. Just bake the bases, add your favourite toppings and grill for a few minutes – it’s that simple!","If the mixture looks too dry to form a rollable dough, add a little water after mashing in <b>step 4.<b>","Simmer the tomato sauce for longer for a thicker consistency.","For a smoother tomato sauce, after simmering in <b>step 7<b>, blend <strong><b>1 min\/speed 5-7,<b> increasing speed gradually<\/strong>."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}